Load Libraries

library(tidyverse)
library(sf)
library(leaflet)
library(htmltools)
library(htmlwidgets)

Read in Data

landmarks <- st_read("http://bostonopendata-boston.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/7a7aca614ad740e99b060e0ee787a228_3.geojson") 
## Reading layer `Boston_Landmarks_Commission__BLC__Landmarks' from data source `http://bostonopendata-boston.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/7a7aca614ad740e99b060e0ee787a228_3.geojson' using driver `GeoJSON'
## Simple feature collection with 172 features and 18 fields
## geometry type:  MULTIPOLYGON
## dimension:      XY
## bbox:           xmin: -71.18994 ymin: 42.25131 xmax: -71.02662 ymax: 42.38096
## geographic CRS: WGS 84

Polygon Display

landmarks_map <- leaflet(landmarks) %>%
  addProviderTiles(providers$Stamen) %>%
  addPolygons(fillColor = "green", stroke = FALSE) %>%
  addControl("Boston Landmark Commission Landmarks", position = "topright") %>%
  addControl('<a href="https://data.boston.gov/dataset/boston-landmarks-commission-blc-landmarks">Data Source</a>',
             position = "bottomleft")

landmarks_map
landmarks$label <- paste(landmarks$Name_of_Pr, "<br>", "Date Designated", landmarks$Date_Desig) %>%
  lapply(htmltools::HTML)

landmarks_map <- leaflet(landmarks) %>%
  addProviderTiles(providers$Stamen) %>%
  addPolygons(fillColor = "green", stroke = FALSE,
              highlightOptions = highlightOptions(fillColor = "darkgreen", 
                                                  fillOpacity = 1),
              label = ~label) %>%
  addControl("Boston Landmark Commission Landmarks", position = "topright") %>%
  addControl('<a href="https://data.boston.gov/dataset/boston-landmarks-commission-blc-landmarks">Data Source</a>',
             position = "bottomleft")

landmarks_map
